# Contributing to quantum_simulator

Welcome! We are excited that you're interested in contributing to the `quantum_simulator` project.

Whether you're fixing a bug, improving documentation, or suggesting new features, your help is greatly appreciated.

## How to Contribute

1. **Fork the repository**  
   Go to [https://github.com/ms1963/quantum_simulator](https://github.com/ms1963/quantum_simulator)  
   Click the “Fork” button to create your own copy.

2. **Clone your fork**
       git clone https://github.com/your-username/quantum_simulator.git
       cd quantum_simulator

3. **Create a new branch**
       git checkout -b your-feature-name

4. **Make your changes**  
   Commit descriptive messages and write clear, maintainable code.

5. **Run tests**  
   Make sure everything works before submitting.

6. **Push and open a pull request**
       git push origin your-feature-name

   Then visit your fork on GitHub and click “Compare & Pull Request”.

## Code Style and Quality

- Follow idiomatic Python and PEP8 guidelines.
- Comment your code meaningfully.
- Include or update docstrings.
- Prefer pure functions and well-isolated modules when possible.

## Reporting Issues

If you discover a bug or have a feature request:
- Search [existing issues](https://github.com/ms1963/quantum_simulator/issues) first.
- If it doesn’t exist, open a [new issue](https://github.com/ms1963/quantum_simulator/issues/new).

Please include:
- A clear description of the problem or idea.
- Steps to reproduce (for bugs).
- Relevant logs or screenshots if needed.

## Contributor License

By contributing, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the MIT License as specified in the `LICENSE` file.

Thank you for helping improve `quantum_simulator`!
